Hi there! I am Sigrid Stensvold, a Minneapolis-based designer and web developer and graduate student at Minneapolis College of Art and Design.

When I am not working on schoolwork or freelance graphic design and illustration projects, you might find me attempting to garden, bicycling around South Minneapolis, or whipping up a meal with local food.

attempting multi-faceted millenial with interests ranging from anthropology and design, to local food and bicycle touring — my aim is to create striking and exciting designs that effortlessly convey meaning and facilitate understanding between people.

Experiences

My professional experiences are as varied as my interests. With background in anthropology, content marketing, graphic design, museum exhibit design, web design, and front-end web development — I approach design problems from an interdisciplinary perspective.

Peruse my resume...

Skills and Services

Looking for a fresh perspective on an upcoming project? Need help in one of the following design areas?

  • Print
  • Web
  • Mobile
  • Logo
  • User experience
  • Front-end web development

Let me help make your vision a reality. Get in touch.
